Bio-LITE-Taxonomy-NCBI

This module provides easy and efficient access to the NCBI taxonomy with minimal dependencies and without intermediary databases. Also allows fast mappings between NCBIs GIs and Taxids.

This module is not part of the Bioperl bundle.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Bio::LITE::Taxonomy::NCBI

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Bio-LITE-Taxonomy-NCBI

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Bio-LITE-Taxonomy-NCBI

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Bio-LITE-Taxonomy-NCBI

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Bio-LITE-Taxonomy-NCBI/


